f which are named from Old English <i>prēost</i> ‘priest’ + <i>cot</i> ‘cottage’, ‘dwelling’. The surname is most common in Lancashire, and so it seems likely that the first of these places is the most frequent source. It is also present in Ireland, being recorded there first in the 15th century.","History: John Prescott of Standish, Lancaster, England, arrived in NewEngland in 1640 and in 1643 was one of the first settlers ofLancaster, MA. His descendants include several prominent Americans ofthe revolutionary war, including Samuel Prescott, born in Concord, MA,in 1751, whose fame lies in completing the midnight ride of warning in1775 after Paul Revere was captured."],"variants":[{"name":"Prescod","meanings":["English (Durham): variant of   Prescott  ."]}]},{"name":"Anne","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Pet form of   Ann   or   Anne ."],"variants":[{"name":"Anni","meanings":["Pet form of   Ann   or   Anne ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Anne Prescott was born in 1382, in Standish, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Sir James Bradshaigh KN. She died in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1382–Unknown":"1382–Surnud","1378–1425":"1378–1425","1408–1446":"1408–1446","1382–Female":"1382–Surnud","1425":"1425","1446":"1446","1378":"1378","1382":"1382","1408":"1408","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Driby Manor, Standish, Lancashire":"Standish, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1382–Unknown":"1382–Kuollut","1378–1425":"1378–1425","1408–1446":"1408–1446","1382–Female":"1382–Kuollut","1425":"1425","1446":"1446","1378":"1378","1382":"1382","1408":"1408","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Driby Manor, Standish, Lancashire":"Standish, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1382–Unknown":"1382–Décédée","1378–1425":"1378–1425","1408–1446":"1408–1446","1382–Female":"1382–Décédée","1425":"1425","1446":"1446","1378":"1378","1382"